{"award_age":61.0,"bio_image":"full\/332717959180a66ef3f0d41454ffd692479de055.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"Ireland","date_of_birth":"1937-01-18T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/5\/5c\/John_Hume_2008.jpg\/220px-John_Hume_2008.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hume","mini_bio":"<p><b>John Hume<\/b>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_St._Gregory_the_Great\" title=\"Order of St. Gregory the Great\">KCSG<\/a> (born 18 January 1937) is an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Irish_people\" title=\"Irish people\">Irish<\/a> former politician from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Derry\" title=\"Derry\">Derry<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Northern_Ireland\" title=\"Northern Ireland\">Northern Ireland<\/a>. He was a founding member of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Social_Democratic_and_Labour_Party\" title=\"Social Democratic and Labour Party\">Social Democratic and Labour Party<\/a>, and was co-recipient of the 1998 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a>, with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/David_Trimble,_Baron_Trimble\" title=\"David Trimble, Baron Trimble\" class=\"mw-redirect\">David Trimble<\/a>.<\/p><p>He was the second leader of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Social_Democratic_and_Labour_Party\" title=\"Social Democratic and Labour Party\">Social Democratic and Labour Party<\/a> (SDLP), a position he held from 1979 until 2001. He has served as a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Member_of_the_European_Parliament\" title=\"Member of the European Parliament\">Member of the European Parliament<\/a> and a Member of the British Parliament, as well as a member of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Northern_Ireland_Assembly\" title=\"Northern Ireland Assembly\">Northern Ireland Assembly<\/a>.<\/p><p>He is regarded as one of the most important figures in the recent political history of Ireland and one of the architects of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Northern_Ireland_peace_process\" title=\"Northern Ireland peace process\">Northern Ireland peace process<\/a>. He is also a recipient of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Gandhi_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Gandhi Peace Prize\">Gandhi Peace Prize<\/a> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Martin_Luther_King\" title=\"Martin Luther King\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Martin Luther King<\/a> Award, the only recipient of the three major peace awards. In 2010 he was named \"<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ireland%27s_Greatest\" title=\"Ireland's Greatest\">Ireland's Greatest<\/a>\" in a public poll by Irish national broadcaster RT\u00c9 to find the greatest person in Ireland's history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hume#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2012, Pope <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Benedict_XVI\" title=\"Benedict XVI\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Benedict XVI<\/a> made Hume a Knight Commander of the Papal <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_St._Gregory_the_Great\" title=\"Order of St. Gregory the Great\">Order of St. Gregory the Great<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hume#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"John Hume","place_of_birth":"Derry City ,  Northern Ireland","place_of_death":null,"text":"John Hume , Peace, 1998","year":1998.0}